](https://img.shields.io/pypi/status/monaco-qt.svg)](https://github.com/DaelonSuzuka/monaco-qt/)\r\n\r\nThe [monaco text editor](https://github.com/microsoft/monaco-editor) deployed as a Qt Widget.\r\n\r\nUses QWebEngineView to load a custom web page containing an instance of monaco.\r\n\r\n# Installation\r\n\r\n`pip install monaco-qt`\r\n\r\nThen, in your qt application:\r\n\r\n```py\r\nfrom monaco import MonacoWidget\r\n\r\nmonaco_widget = MonacoWidget()\r\nmonaco_widget.setText('foo')\r\n```\r\n\r\n# Known Issues\r\n\r\n- Pyinstaller doesn't automatically include the monaco typescript files.\r\n- Very little of the monaco-editor API has been exposed to python so far\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "monaco", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "monaco._pyinstaller_hooks_dir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "monaco.MonacoWidget", "xref": {"fqname": "monaco.monaco_widget.MonacoWidget", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "monaco._pyinstaller", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "monaco._pyinstaller.hook-monaco", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "monaco._pyinstaller.hook-monaco.datas", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "monaco.monaco_widget", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "monaco.monaco_widget.index", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monaco.monaco_widget.raw_html", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "monaco.monaco_widget.BaseBridge", "bases": ["QObject"], "methods": [{"name": "monaco.monaco_widget.BaseBridge.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "parent", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "monaco.monaco_widget.BaseBridge.send_to_js", "asynchronous": false, "params": 